<TITLE> Thunderbolt kills 4 in Chittagong </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 3 (bdnews24.com)  Four members of the same family died and three others were injured after a thunderbolt struck them at Motin Nagar under Bhujpur Police Station in Chittagong Tuesday, a police official said. The dead are Bozlu Miah, 80, his son Motin, 30, Motin's son Jahangir, 10 and niece Jahanara Begum, 8. The injured were rushed to Nazirhat health complex. Bhujpur police chief Md Mainuddin told bdnews24.com the thunderbolt struck the house of Bozlu Miah at around 11:30 am while it was raining, killing the four inmates instantly and wounding three others of the family. bdnews24.c
